criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Previously diagnosed (at least 6 months before enrolment) hypoparathyroidism which
             required daily calcium (≥1000mg/die) and calcitriol therapy;

          -  Signed informed consent to participate in the study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Transient hypoparathyroidism;

          -  History of neoplasms, radiotherapy or chemotherapy in the last 5 years;

          -  Clinical or laboratory signs of significant respiratory, hepatobiliary, or pancreatic
             disease;

          -  Severe infections, surgery, trauma requiring hospitalization within 3 months before
             enrolment;

          -  Severe chronic kidney disease (stage 4-5);

          -  Any active blood or rheumatic disorders in the last 5 years
